---
import Standalone from "../../layouts/Standalone.astro";
---

<Standalone
  title="Flow Health Monitor — AI Agent for Klaviyo | Email Pulse"
  description="The Flow Health Monitor audits every Klaviyo flow in your account, classifies each one by real incremental impact, and delivers prioritized tasks to your team — automatically."
>

  <!-- ========================================
       DEMO BANNER
       ======================================== -->
  <div class="bg-kd-navy text-white text-center py-3 px-6">
    <span class="font-aktiv font-semibold text-[11px] md:text-[12px] tracking-[2px] uppercase">Demo &mdash; Product Page</span>
    <span class="font-montserrat font-light text-white/60 text-[11px] md:text-[12px] tracking-[0.5px] ml-2 hidden md:inline">Flow Health Monitor by Email Pulse. AI-powered Klaviyo flow audits.</span>
  </div>

  <!-- ========================================
       HERO
       ======================================== -->
  <section class="hero-gradient relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute -left-20 top-16 w-[380px] h-[380px] opacity-30 pointer-events-none">
      <img src="/images/home/decorative/bg-circle-left.png" alt="" class="w-full h-full object-contain" aria-hidden="true" />
    </div>
    <div class="absolute -right-16 -bottom-16 w-[300px] h-[300px] opacity-20 pointer-events-none">
      <img src="/images/home/decorative/bg-circle.png" alt="" class="w-full h-full object-contain" aria-hidden="true" />
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto px-6 py-20 md:py-28 relative z-10">
      <span class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up font-montserrat text-kd-gold font-medium text-[13px] tracking-[1.4px] mb-5 block uppercase">AI Agent for Klaviyo</span>

      <h1 class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-100 font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[28px] md:text-[48px] font-bold leading-[36px] md:leading-[58px] tracking-[1px] md:tracking-[1.8px] mb-6">
        Your flows are either making money or wasting it.<br class="hidden md:block" /> This agent tells you which.
      </h1>

      <p class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-200 font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[16px] md:text-[18px] leading-[26px] md:leading-[30px] tracking-[0.8px] mb-10 max-w-[640px]">
        The Flow Health Monitor audits every Klaviyo flow in your account, classifies each one by real incremental impact, and delivers prioritized tasks to your team &mdash; automatically.
      </p>

      <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-300 flex items-center gap-3 flex-wrap">
        <a href="#" class="btn-gold py-4 px-8 rounded-lg text-[14px] md:text-[15px] tracking-[1.4px] inline-flex items-center gap-2">
          Start Free &rarr;
        </a>
        <a href="#how-it-works" class="font-montserrat font-medium text-kd-navy text-[14px] md:text-[15px] tracking-[0.8px] py-4 px-6 hover:text-kd-gold transition-colors">
          See how it works
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========================================
       PROBLEM: DATA VS INSIGHT
       ======================================== -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white px-6">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[22px] md:text-[32px] font-semibold tracking-[1px] leading-[30px] md:leading-[42px] mb-5">
        You already have the data. The problem is what to do with it.
      </h2>

      <p class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-100 font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[15px] md:text-[16px] leading-[26px] tracking-[0.8px] mb-4">
        Klaviyo dashboards show you open rates, click rates, revenue per recipient. But they don&rsquo;t tell you what any of it <em>means</em> for a specific flow &mdash; or what to do next.
      </p>
      <p class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-200 font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[15px] md:text-[16px] leading-[26px] tracking-[0.8px] mb-8">
        You can connect Claude to Klaviyo&rsquo;s MCP and ask it to audit your flows. But here&rsquo;s what actually happens:
      </p>

      <!-- Versus Cards -->
      <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-300 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <span class="font-aktiv text-red-500 text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[1.2px] uppercase block mb-3">What Claude says Monday</span>
          <code class="font-mono text-[13px] leading-[1.8] text-kd-grey whitespace-pre-wrap block">Your Browse Abandonment flow shows
strong engagement. Open rate of 38%
is healthy. Consider A/B testing
subject lines for improvement.</code>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <span class="font-aktiv text-emerald-600 text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[1.2px] uppercase block mb-3">What Claude says Wednesday</span>
          <code class="font-mono text-[13px] leading-[1.8] text-kd-grey whitespace-pre-wrap block">Your Browse Abandonment flow is
underperforming. At 38% open rate
and 0.3% conversion, this flow
needs significant restructuring.</code>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-400 font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey/60 text-[13px] md:text-[14px] leading-[22px] tracking-[0.5px] mt-6">
        Same flow. Same data. Different answer. LLMs interpret numbers probabilistically &mdash; they don&rsquo;t have fixed rules for what &ldquo;good&rdquo; or &ldquo;bad&rdquo; means in your account. The Flow Health Monitor fixes this with deterministic classification that produces the same answer every time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========================================
       CLASSIFICATION: FOUR CATEGORIES
       ======================================== -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 px-6" style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, #F6EFE6 0%, #FAFAFA 100%);">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[22px] md:text-[32px] font-semibold tracking-[1px] leading-[30px] md:leading-[42px] mb-4">
        Every flow gets classified. No ambiguity.
      </h2>
      <p class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-100 font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[15px] md:text-[16px] leading-[26px] tracking-[0.8px] mb-8">
        Instead of generic benchmarks, the agent uses <strong class="font-medium text-kd-navy">uplift modeling</strong> &mdash; comparing shoppers influenced by each flow against those who weren&rsquo;t &mdash; to measure true incremental impact. Every flow lands in one of four categories:
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
        <!-- Sure Shot -->
        <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-100 bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <span class="inline-block bg-emerald-500 text-white text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[1px] uppercase px-3 py-1 rounded-md mb-3">Sure Shot</span>
          <h3 class="font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[16px] md:text-[17px] font-semibold tracking-[0.5px] mb-2">Protect it</h3>
          <p class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[14px] md:text-[15px] leading-[24px] tracking-[0.5px]">High engagement lift + high revenue lift. This flow is generating real incremental value. Document what works. Don&rsquo;t touch it unnecessarily.</p>
        </div>
        <!-- Persuadable -->
        <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-200 bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <span class="inline-block bg-blue-500 text-white text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[1px] uppercase px-3 py-1 rounded-md mb-3">Persuadable</span>
          <h3 class="font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[16px] md:text-[17px] font-semibold tracking-[0.5px] mb-2">Optimize it</h3>
          <p class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[14px] md:text-[15px] leading-[24px] tracking-[0.5px]">Engagement is there but revenue isn&rsquo;t following. Or vice versa. This is your highest-ROI optimization opportunity.</p>
        </div>
        <!-- Sleeping Dog -->
        <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-300 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <span class="inline-block bg-amber-500 text-white text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[1px] uppercase px-3 py-1 rounded-md mb-3">Sleeping Dog</span>
          <h3 class="font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[16px] md:text-[17px] font-semibold tracking-[0.5px] mb-2">Leave it alone</h3>
          <p class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[14px] md:text-[15px] leading-[24px] tracking-[0.5px]">Low engagement, but still converting the people it reaches. Tweaking this will likely hurt more than help. Monitor, don&rsquo;t optimize.</p>
        </div>
        <!-- Lost Cause -->
        <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-400 bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <span class="inline-block bg-red-500 text-white text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[1px] uppercase px-3 py-1 rounded-md mb-3">Lost Cause</span>
          <h3 class="font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[16px] md:text-[17px] font-semibold tracking-[0.5px] mb-2">Fix it or kill it</h3>
          <p class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[14px] md:text-[15px] leading-[24px] tracking-[0.5px]">Low engagement. Low revenue lift. This flow is consuming resources without generating incremental value. Pause, redesign, or remove.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========================================
       OUTPUT TABLE
       ======================================== -->
  <section id="how-it-works" class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white px-6">
    <div class="max-w-[960px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[22px] md:text-[32px] font-semibold tracking-[1px] leading-[30px] md:leading-[42px] mb-4">
        Here&rsquo;s what the agent actually produces.
      </h2>
      <p class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-100 font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[15px] md:text-[16px] leading-[26px] tracking-[0.8px] mb-8">
        For an account with 8 active flows, a single run generates a complete audit with prioritized actions:
      </p>

      <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-200 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-gray-200 text-[14px] md:text-[15px]">
          <thead class="bg-kd-navy">
            <tr>
              <th class="text-left py-3.5 px-4 text-white font-montserrat font-semibold text-[12px] tracking-[1px] uppercase">Flow</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3.5 px-4 text-white font-montserrat font-semibold text-[12px] tracking-[1px] uppercase">Classification</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3.5 px-4 text-white font-montserrat font-semibold text-[12px] tracking-[1px] uppercase">Priority</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3.5 px-4 text-white font-montserrat font-semibold text-[12px] tracking-[1px] uppercase">Action</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey">
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4 font-medium text-kd-navy">Abandoned Cart</td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4"><span class="inline-block bg-emerald-500 text-white text-[10px] font-bold tracking-[0.8px] uppercase px-2 py-0.5 rounded">Sure Shot</span></td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4">Protect</td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4 text-[13px] md:text-[14px]">Generating $4.82 RPR with 12% placed order rate. Document success factors. Consider scaling to SMS.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4 font-medium text-kd-navy">Welcome Series</td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4"><span class="inline-block bg-blue-500 text-white text-[10px] font-bold tracking-[0.8px] uppercase px-2 py-0.5 rounded">Persuadable</span></td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4">Optimize</td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4 text-[13px] md:text-[14px]">Strong opens (52%) but low conversion (1.8%). Test stronger first-purchase incentive in email 2.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4 font-medium text-kd-navy">Post-Purchase</td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4"><span class="inline-block bg-blue-500 text-white text-[10px] font-bold tracking-[0.8px] uppercase px-2 py-0.5 rounded">Persuadable</span></td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4">Optimize</td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4 text-[13px] md:text-[14px]">Cross-sell timing is off. Move product rec from day 3 to day 7 based on average fulfillment window.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4 font-medium text-kd-navy">VIP Repeat</td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4"><span class="inline-block bg-amber-500 text-white text-[10px] font-bold tracking-[0.8px] uppercase px-2 py-0.5 rounded">Sleeping Dog</span></td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4">Monitor</td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4 text-[13px] md:text-[14px]">Low open rate (18%) but $4.20 RPR. This audience buys regardless. Don&rsquo;t over-optimize.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4 font-medium text-kd-navy">Browse Abandonment</td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4"><span class="inline-block bg-red-500 text-white text-[10px] font-bold tracking-[0.8px] uppercase px-2 py-0.5 rounded">Lost Cause</span></td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4">Fix / Kill</td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4 text-[13px] md:text-[14px]">12% open, 0.3% conversion, no measurable revenue lift. Pause and redesign with better product targeting.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4 font-medium text-kd-navy">Winback</td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4"><span class="inline-block bg-red-500 text-white text-[10px] font-bold tracking-[0.8px] uppercase px-2 py-0.5 rounded">Lost Cause</span></td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4">Fix / Kill</td>
              <td class="py-3.5 px-4 text-[13px] md:text-[14px]">Sending to 120-day lapsed with generic content. Segment by last purchase category or sunset.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-300 font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey/60 text-[13px] md:text-[14px] leading-[22px] tracking-[0.5px] mt-5">
        Each row becomes a task in your project management tool (Asana, Slack, or your CRM) with the classification as a tag, the priority level, and the specific recommendation as the task description. Your team opens their board Monday morning and knows exactly what to work on.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========================================
       PM TOOL DELIVERY (NEW SECTION)
       ======================================== -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 px-6" style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, #FAFAFA 0%, #F6EFE6 100%);">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[22px] md:text-[32px] font-semibold tracking-[1px] leading-[30px] md:leading-[42px] mb-4">
        The audit lands in your project management tool. Not another dashboard.
      </h2>
      <p class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-100 font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[15px] md:text-[16px] leading-[26px] tracking-[0.8px] mb-8">
        Most analytics tools give you a report you have to remember to check. The Flow Health Monitor pushes every finding directly into the tools your team already uses &mdash; as structured, prioritized tasks ready to be assigned and executed.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
        <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-200 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-7 shadow-sm">
          <span class="text-[24px] block mb-3">&#9745;&#65039;</span>
          <h3 class="font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[16px] md:text-[18px] font-semibold tracking-[0.5px] mb-3">Asana, ClickUp, Monday</h3>
          <p class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[14px] md:text-[15px] leading-[24px] tracking-[0.5px]">
            Each flow finding becomes a task with the classification tag, priority level, supporting metrics, and a specific recommendation your team can act on immediately. No copy-pasting from a PDF. No translating a chart into a to-do list.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-300 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-7 shadow-sm">
          <span class="text-[24px] block mb-3">&#128172;</span>
          <h3 class="font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[16px] md:text-[18px] font-semibold tracking-[0.5px] mb-3">Slack, Teams, Email</h3>
          <p class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[14px] md:text-[15px] leading-[24px] tracking-[0.5px]">
            Weekly audit summaries delivered to your channel or inbox. Flag critical issues (Lost Causes, broken triggers) in real time so nothing sits unnoticed until the next monthly review.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-400 font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey/60 text-[13px] md:text-[14px] leading-[22px] tracking-[0.5px] mt-6">
        This is the difference between an audit your team reads and an audit your team acts on. The output format is the product.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========================================
       SIX STEPS
       ======================================== -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white px-6">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[22px] md:text-[32px] font-semibold tracking-[1px] leading-[30px] md:leading-[42px] mb-8">
        Six steps. Fully automated.
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-0">
        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-100 flex gap-5 py-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-kd-cream rounded-lg border-2 border-kd-gold/30 flex items-center justify-center font-aktiv font-bold text-[14px] text-kd-gold">1</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[16px] md:text-[17px] font-semibold tracking-[0.5px] mb-1">Pull flow data</h3>
            <p class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[14px] md:text-[15px] leading-[24px] tracking-[0.5px]">The agent calls Email Pulse&rsquo;s evaluation engine with your Klaviyo account, pulling metrics, setup quality scores, and performance scores for every active flow.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-200 flex gap-5 py-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-kd-cream rounded-lg border-2 border-kd-gold/30 flex items-center justify-center font-aktiv font-bold text-[14px] text-kd-gold">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[16px] md:text-[17px] font-semibold tracking-[0.5px] mb-1">Classify each flow</h3>
            <p class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[14px] md:text-[15px] leading-[24px] tracking-[0.5px]">Deterministic logic applies the uplift matrix &mdash; engagement lift &times; monetization lift &mdash; to classify each flow as Sure Shot, Persuadable, Sleeping Dog, or Lost Cause. Same data, same answer, every time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-300 flex gap-5 py-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-kd-cream rounded-lg border-2 border-kd-gold/30 flex items-center justify-center font-aktiv font-bold text-[14px] text-kd-gold">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[16px] md:text-[17px] font-semibold tracking-[0.5px] mb-1">Score setup quality</h3>
            <p class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[14px] md:text-[15px] leading-[24px] tracking-[0.5px]">Each flow is evaluated against completeness criteria: trigger configuration, message setup, timing logic, tracking, and status. Missing elements are flagged as quick wins.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Step 4 -->
        <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-100 flex gap-5 py-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-kd-cream rounded-lg border-2 border-kd-gold/30 flex items-center justify-center font-aktiv font-bold text-[14px] text-kd-gold">4</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[16px] md:text-[17px] font-semibold tracking-[0.5px] mb-1">Compare to flow-type benchmarks</h3>
            <p class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[14px] md:text-[15px] leading-[24px] tracking-[0.5px]">Performance is checked against flow-type-specific thresholds &mdash; not generic industry averages. An abandoned cart flow is held to a different standard than a winback flow.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Step 5 -->
        <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-200 flex gap-5 py-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-kd-cream rounded-lg border-2 border-kd-gold/30 flex items-center justify-center font-aktiv font-bold text-[14px] text-kd-gold">5</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[16px] md:text-[17px] font-semibold tracking-[0.5px] mb-1">Generate priorities</h3>
            <p class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[14px] md:text-[15px] leading-[24px] tracking-[0.5px]">Flows are tiered: Sure Shots to protect and Lost Causes to fix are Tier 1. Persuadables are Tier 2. Sleeping Dogs are Tier 3. Your team works top-down.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Step 6 -->
        <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-300 flex gap-5 py-6">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-kd-cream rounded-lg border-2 border-kd-gold/30 flex items-center justify-center font-aktiv font-bold text-[14px] text-kd-gold">6</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[16px] md:text-[17px] font-semibold tracking-[0.5px] mb-1">Deliver tasks</h3>
            <p class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[14px] md:text-[15px] leading-[24px] tracking-[0.5px]">Prioritized action items are pushed to Asana, Slack, or your CRM. Each task includes the classification, specific recommendation, and supporting data.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========================================
       WHY THIS ISN'T ANOTHER AI WRAPPER
       ======================================== -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 px-6" style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, #F6EFE6 0%, #FAFAFA 100%);">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up font-aktiv text-kd-navy text-[22px] md:text-[32px] font-semibold tracking-[1px] leading-[30px] md:leading-[42px] mb-6">
        Why this isn&rsquo;t just another AI wrapper.
      </h2>

      <div class="animate-on-scroll fade-in-up delay-100 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-8 shadow-sm">
        <p class="font-montserrat font-light text-kd-grey text-[15px] md:text-[16px] leading-[26px] tracking-[0.8px] mb-4">
          <strong class="font-medium text-kd-navy">Most &ldquo;AI audit&rdquo; tools ask an LLM to look at your numbers and tell you what it thinks.</strong> That&rsquo;s a book report, not an audit. The output changes every time you run it. You can&rsquo;t automate on top of something unreliable.
        </p>
